The White House has announced the program, activities, and talent line-up for the 2014 White House Easter Egg Roll. The event will take place on April 21 and is focused on promoting health and wellness with the theme, "Hop into Healthy, Swing into Shape." Activities will include live music, sports courts, cooking stations, storytelling, and Easter egg rolling. The talent line-up includes 12-year-old singing sensation Cam Anthony, DJ Beauty & the Beatz, Ariana Grande, Candice Glover, R5 featuring Ross Lynch, DJ Young1, and characters from Sesame Street. There will also be performances by the United States Marine Corps Band and readings by Jim Carrey, Miss America 2014 Nina Davuluri, former NFL player and NASA astronaut Leland Melvin, and others. The event will feature healthy eating demonstrations, sports activities, dance parties, and more. Over 30,000 people from all 50 states and the District of Columbia have received tickets to the event.